ABUJA – A former Senator who represented Edo North Senatorial district, Yisa Braimoh has described Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo state as a “resourceful and great achiever”. In a statement released on Friday in commemoration of the 65th birthday anniversary of Governor Obaseki, the Senator noted the worthy contributions of the governor to the rapid development of the state and also his selfless sacrifice in bringing dividends of democracy closer to the people. He said Obaseki has placed the people of Edo State at the centre of governance by regularly embarking on policies and people-oriented projects that support human and capital development. “As the Governor turns 65, I can attest that his loyalty and dedication to duty have been most exemplary, especially in arrears of human capital development. “Your developmental projects which are people-oriented have brought dividends of democracy closer to the people” Senator Braimoh. “Besides, your regular consultations and interface with the people and other government structures to ensure synergy and harmony that put the welfare and well-being of citizens first remain the focus of his administration. Senator Braimoh, who is the Serki Musulumi of Afenmai land and the Ininame of Ihievbe Kingdom, extolled the Governor’s courage, humility and resourcefulness, praying that the Almighty God will continue to grant him the strength, wisdom and good health to serve Edo state, the nation and humanity. “He was born on the 1st of July and has always come first in all his human endeavours. His name is Godwin and he is indeed a winner any day anytime.”